1313 /* MIT license */
1314 var cssKeywords = __webpack_require__(10626);
1315 
1316 // NOTE: conversions should only return primitive values (i.e. arrays, or
1317 //       values that give correct `typeof` results).
1318 //       do not use box values types (i.e. Number(), String(), etc.)
1319 
1320 var reverseKeywords = {};
1321 for (var key in cssKeywords) {
1322 	if (cssKeywords.hasOwnProperty(key)) {
1323 		reverseKeywords[cssKeywords[key]] = key;
1324 	}
1325 }
1326 
1327 var convert = module.exports = {
1328 	rgb: {channels: 3, labels: 'rgb'},
1329 	hsl: {channels: 3, labels: 'hsl'},
1330 	hsv: {channels: 3, labels: 'hsv'},
1331 	hwb: {channels: 3, labels: 'hwb'},
1332 	cmyk: {channels: 4, labels: 'cmyk'},
1333 	xyz: {channels: 3, labels: 'xyz'},
1334 	lab: {channels: 3, labels: 'lab'},
1335 	lch: {channels: 3, labels: 'lch'},
1336 	hex: {channels: 1, labels: ['hex']},
1337 	keyword: {channels: 1, labels: ['keyword']},
1338 	ansi16: {channels: 1, labels: ['ansi16']},
1339 	ansi256: {channels: 1, labels: ['ansi256']},
1340 	hcg: {channels: 3, labels: ['h', 'c', 'g']},
1341 	apple: {channels: 3, labels: ['r16', 'g16', 'b16']},
1342 	gray: {channels: 1, labels: ['gray']}
1343 };
1344 
1345 // hide .channels and .labels properties
1346 for (var model in convert) {
1347 	if (convert.hasOwnProperty(model)) {
1348 		if (!('channels' in convert[model])) {
1349 			throw new Error('missing channels property: ' + model);
1350 		}
1351 
1352 		if (!('labels' in convert[model])) {
1353 			throw new Error('missing channel labels property: ' + model);
1354 		}
1355 
1356 		if (convert[model].labels.length !== convert[model].channels) {
1357 			throw new Error('channel and label counts mismatch: ' + model);
1358 		}
1359 
1360 		var channels = convert[model].channels;
1361 		var labels = convert[model].labels;
1362 		delete convert[model].channels;
1363 		delete convert[model].labels;
1364 		Object.defineProperty(convert[model], 'channels', {value: channels});
1365 		Object.defineProperty(convert[model], 'labels', {value: labels});
1366 	}
1367 }
1368 
1369 convert.rgb.hsl = function (rgb) {
1370 	var r = rgb[0] / 255;
1371 	var g = rgb[1] / 255;
1372 	var b = rgb[2] / 255;
1373 	var min = Math.min(r, g, b);
1374 	var max = Math.max(r, g, b);
1375 	var delta = max - min;
1376 	var h;
1377 	var s;
1378 	var l;
1379 
1380 	if (max === min) {
1381 		h = 0;
1382 	} else if (r === max) {
1383 		h = (g - b) / delta;
1384 	} else if (g === max) {
1385 		h = 2 + (b - r) / delta;
1386 	} else if (b === max) {
1387 		h = 4 + (r - g) / delta;
1388 	}
1389 
1390 	h = Math.min(h * 60, 360);
1391 
1392 	if (h < 0) {
1393 		h += 360;
1394 	}
1395 
1396 	l = (min + max) / 2;
1397 
1398 	if (max === min) {
1399 		s = 0;
1400 	} else if (l <= 0.5) {
1401 		s = delta / (max + min);
1402 	} else {
1403 		s = delta / (2 - max - min);
1404 	}
1405 
1406 	return [h, s * 100, l * 100];
1407 };
1408 
1409 convert.rgb.hsv = function (rgb) {
1410 	var rdif;
1411 	var gdif;
1412 	var bdif;
1413 	var h;
1414 	var s;
1415 
1416 	var r = rgb[0] / 255;
1417 	var g = rgb[1] / 255;
1418 	var b = rgb[2] / 255;
1419 	var v = Math.max(r, g, b);
1420 	var diff = v - Math.min(r, g, b);
1421 	var diffc = function (c) {
1422 		return (v - c) / 6 / diff + 1 / 2;
1423 	};
1424 
1425 	if (diff === 0) {
1426 		h = s = 0;
1427 	} else {
1428 		s = diff / v;
1429 		rdif = diffc(r);
1430 		gdif = diffc(g);
1431 		bdif = diffc(b);
1432 
1433 		if (r === v) {
1434 			h = bdif - gdif;
1435 		} else if (g === v) {
1436 			h = (1 / 3) + rdif - bdif;
1437 		} else if (b === v) {
1438 			h = (2 / 3) + gdif - rdif;
1439 		}
1440 		if (h < 0) {
1441 			h += 1;
1442 		} else if (h > 1) {
1443 			h -= 1;
1444 		}
1445 	}
1446 
1447 	return [
1448 		h * 360,
1449 		s * 100,
1450 		v * 100
1451 	];
1452 };

1454 convert.rgb.hwb = function (rgb) {
1455 	var r = rgb[0];
1456 	var g = rgb[1];
1457 	var b = rgb[2];
1458 	var h = convert.rgb.hsl(rgb)[0];
1459 	var w = 1 / 255 * Math.min(r, Math.min(g, b));
1460 
1461 	b = 1 - 1 / 255 * Math.max(r, Math.max(g, b));
1462 
1463 	return [h, w * 100, b * 100];
1464 };

1483 /**
1484  * See https://en.m.wikipedia.org/wiki/Euclidean_distance#Squared_Euclidean_distance
1485  * */
1486 function comparativeDistance(x, y) {
1487 	return (
1488 		Math.pow(x[0] - y[0], 2) +
1489 		Math.pow(x[1] - y[1], 2) +
1490 		Math.pow(x[2] - y[2], 2)
1491 	);
1492 }

1494 convert.rgb.keyword = function (rgb) {
1495 	var reversed = reverseKeywords[rgb];
1496 	if (reversed) {
1497 		return reversed;
1498 	}
1499 
1500 	var currentClosestDistance = Infinity;
1501 	var currentClosestKeyword;
1502 
1503 	for (var keyword in cssKeywords) {
1504 		if (cssKeywords.hasOwnProperty(keyword)) {
1505 			var value = cssKeywords[keyword];
1506 
1507 			// Compute comparative distance
1508 			var distance = comparativeDistance(rgb, value);
1509 
1510 			// Check if its less, if so set as closest
1511 			if (distance < currentClosestDistance) {
1512 				currentClosestDistance = distance;
1513 				currentClosestKeyword = keyword;
1514 			}
1515 		}
1516 	}
1517 
1518 	return currentClosestKeyword;
1519 };

1525 convert.rgb.xyz = function (rgb) {
1526 	var r = rgb[0] / 255;
1527 	var g = rgb[1] / 255;
1528 	var b = rgb[2] / 255;
1529 
1530 	// assume sRGB
1531 	r = r > 0.04045 ? Math.pow(((r + 0.055) / 1.055), 2.4) : (r / 12.92);
1532 	g = g > 0.04045 ? Math.pow(((g + 0.055) / 1.055), 2.4) : (g / 12.92);
1533 	b = b > 0.04045 ? Math.pow(((b + 0.055) / 1.055), 2.4) : (b / 12.92);
1534 
1535 	var x = (r * 0.4124) + (g * 0.3576) + (b * 0.1805);
1536 	var y = (r * 0.2126) + (g * 0.7152) + (b * 0.0722);
1537 	var z = (r * 0.0193) + (g * 0.1192) + (b * 0.9505);
1538 
1539 	return [x * 100, y * 100, z * 100];

1566 convert.hsl.rgb = function (hsl) {
1567 	var h = hsl[0] / 360;
1568 	var s = hsl[1] / 100;
1569 	var l = hsl[2] / 100;
1570 	var t1;
1571 	var t2;
1572 	var t3;
1573 	var rgb;
1574 	var val;
1575 
1576 	if (s === 0) {
1577 		val = l * 255;
1578 		return [val, val, val];
1579 	}
1580 
1581 	if (l < 0.5) {
1582 		t2 = l * (1 + s);
1583 	} else {
1584 		t2 = l + s - l * s;
1585 	}
1586 
1587 	t1 = 2 * l - t2;
1588 
1589 	rgb = [0, 0, 0];
1590 	for (var i = 0; i < 3; i++) {
1591 		t3 = h + 1 / 3 * -(i - 1);
1592 		if (t3 < 0) {
1593 			t3++;
1594 		}
1595 		if (t3 > 1) {
1596 			t3--;
1597 		}
1598 
1599 		if (6 * t3 < 1) {
1600 			val = t1 + (t2 - t1) * 6 * t3;
1601 		} else if (2 * t3 < 1) {
1602 			val = t2;
1603 		} else if (3 * t3 < 2) {
1604 			val = t1 + (t2 - t1) * (2 / 3 - t3) * 6;
1605 		} else {
1606 			val = t1;
1607 		}
1608 
1609 		rgb[i] = val * 255;
1610 	}
1611 
1612 	return rgb;
1613 };

1615 convert.hsl.hsv = function (hsl) {
1616 	var h = hsl[0];
1617 	var s = hsl[1] / 100;
1618 	var l = hsl[2] / 100;
1619 	var smin = s;
1620 	var lmin = Math.max(l, 0.01);
1621 	var sv;
1622 	var v;
1623 
1624 	l *= 2;
1625 	s *= (l <= 1) ? l : 2 - l;
1626 	smin *= lmin <= 1 ? lmin : 2 - lmin;
1627 	v = (l + s) / 2;
1628 	sv = l === 0 ? (2 * smin) / (lmin + smin) : (2 * s) / (l + s);
1629 
1630 	return [h, sv * 100, v * 100];
1631 };

1633 convert.hsv.rgb = function (hsv) {
1634 	var h = hsv[0] / 60;
1635 	var s = hsv[1] / 100;
1636 	var v = hsv[2] / 100;
1637 	var hi = Math.floor(h) % 6;
1638 
1639 	var f = h - Math.floor(h);
1640 	var p = 255 * v * (1 - s);
1641 	var q = 255 * v * (1 - (s * f));
1642 	var t = 255 * v * (1 - (s * (1 - f)));
1643 	v *= 255;
1644 
1645 	switch (hi) {
1646 		case 0:
1647 			return [v, t, p];
1648 		case 1:
1649 			return [q, v, p];
1650 		case 2:
1651 			return [p, v, t];
1652 		case 3:
1653 			return [p, q, v];
1654 		case 4:
1655 			return [t, p, v];
1656 		case 5:
1657 			return [v, p, q];
1658 	}
1659 };

1661 convert.hsv.hsl = function (hsv) {
1662 	var h = hsv[0];
1663 	var s = hsv[1] / 100;
1664 	var v = hsv[2] / 100;
1665 	var vmin = Math.max(v, 0.01);
1666 	var lmin;
1667 	var sl;
1668 	var l;
1669 
1670 	l = (2 - s) * v;
1671 	lmin = (2 - s) * vmin;
1672 	sl = s * vmin;
1673 	sl /= (lmin <= 1) ? lmin : 2 - lmin;
1674 	sl = sl || 0;
1675 	l /= 2;
1676 
1677 	return [h, sl * 100, l * 100];
1678 };

1680 // http://dev.w3.org/csswg/css-color/#hwb-to-rgb
1681 convert.hwb.rgb = function (hwb) {
1682 	var h = hwb[0] / 360;
1683 	var wh = hwb[1] / 100;
1684 	var bl = hwb[2] / 100;
1685 	var ratio = wh + bl;
1686 	var i;
1687 	var v;
1688 	var f;
1689 	var n;
1690 
1691 	// wh + bl cant be > 1
1692 	if (ratio > 1) {
1693 		wh /= ratio;
1694 		bl /= ratio;
1695 	}
1696 
1697 	i = Math.floor(6 * h);
1698 	v = 1 - bl;
1699 	f = 6 * h - i;
1700 
1701 	if ((i & 0x01) !== 0) {
1702 		f = 1 - f;
1703 	}
1704 
1705 	n = wh + f * (v - wh); // linear interpolation
1706 
1707 	var r;
1708 	var g;
1709 	var b;
1710 	switch (i) {
1711 		default:
1712 		case 6:
1713 		case 0: r = v; g = n; b = wh; break;
1714 		case 1: r = n; g = v; b = wh; break;
1715 		case 2: r = wh; g = v; b = n; break;
1716 		case 3: r = wh; g = n; b = v; break;
1717 		case 4: r = n; g = wh; b = v; break;
1718 		case 5: r = v; g = wh; b = n; break;
1719 	}
1720 
1721 	return [r * 255, g * 255, b * 255];
1722 };

1724 convert.cmyk.rgb = function (cmyk) {

1726 	var m = cmyk[1] / 100;
1727 	var y = cmyk[2] / 100;
1728 	var k = cmyk[3] / 100;
1729 	var r;
1730 	var g;
1731 	var b;
1732 
1733 	r = 1 - Math.min(1, c * (1 - k) + k);
1734 	g = 1 - Math.min(1, m * (1 - k) + k);
1735 	b = 1 - Math.min(1, y * (1 - k) + k);
1736 
1737 	return [r * 255, g * 255, b * 255];
1738 };

1766 	g = Math.min(Math.max(0, g), 1);
1767 	b = Math.min(Math.max(0, b), 1);

1856 convert.rgb.ansi16 = function (args) {

1859 	var b = args[2];

1869 		+ ((Math.round(b / 255) << 2)
1870 		| (Math.round(g / 255) << 1)

1874 		ansi += 60;

1886 convert.rgb.ansi256 = function (args) {

1888 	var g = args[1];
1889 	var b = args[2];
1890 
1891 	// we use the extended greyscale palette here, with the exception of
1892 	// black and white. normal palette only has 4 greyscale shades.
1893 	if (r === g && g === b) {
1894 		if (r < 8) {
1895 			return 16;
1896 		}
1897 
1898 		if (r > 248) {
1899 			return 231;
1900 		}

1903 	}
1904 
1905 	var ansi = 16
1906 		+ (36 * Math.round(r / 255 * 5))
1907 		+ (6 * Math.round(g / 255 * 5))
1908 		+ Math.round(b / 255 * 5);

1913 convert.ansi16.rgb = function (args) {
1914 	var color = args % 10;
1915 
1916 	// handle greyscale
1917 	if (color === 0 || color === 7) {
1918 		if (args > 50) {
1919 			color += 3.5;
1920 		}
1921 
1922 		color = color / 10.5 * 255;
1923 
1924 		return [color, color, color];
1925 	}
1926 
1927 	var mult = (~~(args > 50) + 1) * 0.5;
1928 	var r = ((color & 1) * mult) * 255;
1929 	var g = (((color >> 1) & 1) * mult) * 255;
1930 	var b = (((color >> 2) & 1) * mult) * 255;
1931 
1932 	return [r, g, b];
1933 };

1935 convert.ansi256.rgb = function (args) {

1937 	if (args >= 232) {

1939 		return [c, c, c];
1940 	}
1941 
1942 	args -= 16;
1943

1952 convert.rgb.hex = function (args) {
1953 	var integer = ((Math.round(args[0]) & 0xFF) << 16)
1954 		+ ((Math.round(args[1]) & 0xFF) << 8)
1955 		+ (Math.round(args[2]) & 0xFF);

1958 	return '000000'.substring(string.length) + string;

1961 convert.hex.rgb = function (args) {
1962 	var match = args.toString(16).match(/[a-f0-9]{6}|[a-f0-9]{3}/i);
1963 	if (!match) {
1964 		return [0, 0, 0];
1965 	}
1966 
1967 	var colorString = match[0];
1968 
1969 	if (match[0].length === 3) {
1970 		colorString = colorString.split('').map(function (char) {
1971 			return char + char;
1972 		}).join('');
1973 	}
1974 
1975 	var integer = parseInt(colorString, 16);
1976 	var r = (integer >> 16) & 0xFF;
1977 	var g = (integer >> 8) & 0xFF;
1978 	var b = integer & 0xFF;
1979 
1980 	return [r, g, b];
1981 };

1983 convert.rgb.hcg = function (rgb) {
1984 	var r = rgb[0] / 255;
1985 	var g = rgb[1] / 255;
1986 	var b = rgb[2] / 255;
1987 	var max = Math.max(Math.max(r, g), b);
1988 	var min = Math.min(Math.min(r, g), b);
1989 	var chroma = (max - min);
1990 	var grayscale;
1991 	var hue;
1992 
1993 	if (chroma < 1) {
1994 		grayscale = min / (1 - chroma);
1995 	} else {
1996 		grayscale = 0;
1997 	}
1998 
1999 	if (chroma <= 0) {
2000 		hue = 0;
2001 	} else
2002 	if (max === r) {
2003 		hue = ((g - b) / chroma) % 6;
2004 	} else
2005 	if (max === g) {
2006 		hue = 2 + (b - r) / chroma;
2007 	} else {
2008 		hue = 4 + (r - g) / chroma + 4;
2009 	}
2010 
2011 	hue /= 6;
2012 	hue %= 1;
2013 
2014 	return [hue * 360, chroma * 100, grayscale * 100];
2015 };

2017 convert.hsl.hcg = function (hsl) {
2018 	var s = hsl[1] / 100;
2019 	var l = hsl[2] / 100;
2020 	var c = 1;
2021 	var f = 0;
2022 
2023 	if (l < 0.5) {
2024 		c = 2.0 * s * l;
2025 	} else {
2026 		c = 2.0 * s * (1.0 - l);
2027 	}
2028 
2029 	if (c < 1.0) {
2030 		f = (l - 0.5 * c) / (1.0 - c);
2031 	}
2032 
2033 	return [hsl[0], c * 100, f * 100];
2034 };

2039 
2040 	var c = s * v;
2041 	var f = 0;
2042 
2043 	if (c < 1.0) {
2044 		f = (v - c) / (1 - c);
2045 	}
2046

2050 convert.hcg.rgb = function (hcg) {
2051 	var h = hcg[0] / 360;
2052 	var c = hcg[1] / 100;
2053 	var g = hcg[2] / 100;
2054 
2055 	if (c === 0.0) {
2056 		return [g * 255, g * 255, g * 255];
2057 	}
2058 
2059 	var pure = [0, 0, 0];
2060 	var hi = (h % 1) * 6;
2061 	var v = hi % 1;
2062 	var w = 1 - v;
2063 	var mg = 0;
2064 
2065 	switch (Math.floor(hi)) {
2066 		case 0:
2067 			pure[0] = 1; pure[1] = v; pure[2] = 0; break;
2068 		case 1:
2069 			pure[0] = w; pure[1] = 1; pure[2] = 0; break;

2431 /***/ ((module, __unused_webpack_exports, __webpack_require__) => {
2432 
2433 var conversions = __webpack_require__(47297);
2434 
2435 /* 
2436     this function routes a model to all other models. 
2437  
2438     all functions that are routed have a property `.conversion` attached 
2439     to the returned synthetic function. This property is an array 
2440     of strings, each with the steps in between the 'from' and 'to' 
2441     color models (inclusive). 
2442  
2443     conversions that are not possible simply are not included. 
2444 */
2445 
2446 function buildGraph() {
2447 	var graph = {};
2448 	// https://jsperf.com/object-keys-vs-for-in-with-closure/3
2449 	var models = Object.keys(conversions);
2450 
2451 	for (var len = models.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
2452 		graph[models[i]] = {
2453 			// http://jsperf.com/1-vs-infinity
2454 			// micro-opt, but this is simple.
2455 			distance: -1,
2456 			parent: null
2457 		};
2458 	}
2459 
2460 	return graph;
2461 }
2462 
2463 // https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Breadth-first_search
2464 function deriveBFS(fromModel) {
2465 	var graph = buildGraph();
2466 	var queue = [fromModel]; // unshift -> queue -> pop
2467 
2468 	graph[fromModel].distance = 0;
2469 
2470 	while (queue.length) {
2471 		var current = queue.pop();
2472 		var adjacents = Object.keys(conversions[current]);
2473 
2474 		for (var len = adjacents.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
2475 			var adjacent = adjacents[i];
2476 			var node = graph[adjacent];
2477 
2478 			if (node.distance === -1) {
2479 				node.distance = graph[current].distance + 1;
2480 				node.parent = current;
2481 				queue.unshift(adjacent);
2482 			}
2483 		}
2484 	}
2485 
2486 	return graph;
2487 }
2488 
2489 function link(from, to) {
2490 	return function (args) {
2491 		return to(from(args));
2492 	};
2493 }
2494 
2495 function wrapConversion(toModel, graph) {
2496 	var path = [graph[toModel].parent, toModel];
2497 	var fn = conversions[graph[toModel].parent][toModel];
2498 
2499 	var cur = graph[toModel].parent;
2500 	while (graph[cur].parent) {
2501 		path.unshift(graph[cur].parent);
2502 		fn = link(conversions[graph[cur].parent][cur], fn);
2503 		cur = graph[cur].parent;
2504 	}
2505 
2506 	fn.conversion = path;
2507 	return fn;
2508 }
2509 
2510 module.exports = function (fromModel) {
2511 	var graph = deriveBFS(fromModel);
2512 	var conversion = {};
2513 
2514 	var models = Object.keys(graph);
2515 	for (var len = models.length, i = 0; i < len; i++) {
2516 		var toModel = models[i];
2517 		var node = graph[toModel];
2518 
2519 		if (node.parent === null) {
2520 			// no possible conversion, or this node is the source model.
2521 			continue;
2522 		}
2523 
2524 		conversion[toModel] = wrapConversion(toModel, graph);
2525 	}
2526 
2527 	return conversion;
2528 };

2745 	}
2746 
2747 	var abbr = /^#([a-f0-9]{3,4})$/i;

3332 				color1.alpha() * p + color2.alpha() * (1 - p));

3528 /**
3529  * A faster alternative to `Function#apply`, this function invokes `func`
3530  * with the `this` binding of `thisArg` and the arguments of `args`.
3531  *
3532  * @private
3533  * @param {Function} func The function to invoke.
3534  * @param {*} thisArg The `this` binding of `func`.
3535  * @param {Array} args The arguments to invoke `func` with.
3536  * @returns {*} Returns the result of `func`.
3537  */
3538 function apply(func, thisArg, args) {
3539   switch (args.length) {
3540     case 0: return func.call(thisArg);
3541     case 1: return func.call(thisArg, args[0]);
3542     case 2: return func.call(thisArg, args[0], args[1]);
3543     case 3: return func.call(thisArg, args[0], args[1], args[2]);
3544   }
3545   return func.apply(thisArg, args);
3546 }

3792 /**
3793  * Creates an array that is the composition of partially applied arguments,
3794  * placeholders, and provided arguments into a single array of arguments.
3795  *
3796  * @private
3797  * @param {Array} args The provided arguments.
3798  * @param {Array} partials The arguments to prepend to those provided.
3799  * @param {Array} holders The `partials` placeholder indexes.
3800  * @params {boolean} [isCurried] Specify composing for a curried function.
3801  * @returns {Array} Returns the new array of composed arguments.
3802  */
3803 function composeArgs(args, partials, holders, isCurried) {
3804   var argsIndex = -1,
3805       argsLength = args.length,
3806       holdersLength = holders.length,
3807       leftIndex = -1,
3808       leftLength = partials.length,
3809       rangeLength = nativeMax(argsLength - holdersLength, 0),
3810       result = Array(leftLength + rangeLength),
3811       isUncurried = !isCurried;
3812 
3813   while (++leftIndex < leftLength) {
3814     result[leftIndex] = partials[leftIndex];
3815   }
3816   while (++argsIndex < holdersLength) {
3817     if (isUncurried || argsIndex < argsLength) {
3818       result[holders[argsIndex]] = args[argsIndex];
3819     }
3820   }
3821   while (rangeLength--) {
3822     result[leftIndex++] = args[argsIndex++];
3823   }
3824   return result;
3825 }

3827 /**
3828  * This function is like `composeArgs` except that the arguments composition
3829  * is tailored for `_.partialRight`.
3830  *
3831  * @private
3832  * @param {Array} args The provided arguments.
3833  * @param {Array} partials The arguments to append to those provided.
3834  * @param {Array} holders The `partials` placeholder indexes.
3835  * @params {boolean} [isCurried] Specify composing for a curried function.
3836  * @returns {Array} Returns the new array of composed arguments.
3837  */
3838 function composeArgsRight(args, partials, holders, isCurried) {
3839   var argsIndex = -1,
3840       argsLength = args.length,
3841       holdersIndex = -1,
3842       holdersLength = holders.length,
3843       rightIndex = -1,
3844       rightLength = partials.length,
3845       rangeLength = nativeMax(argsLength - holdersLength, 0),
3846       result = Array(rangeLength + rightLength),
3847       isUncurried = !isCurried;
3848 
3849   while (++argsIndex < rangeLength) {
3850     result[argsIndex] = args[argsIndex];
3851   }
3852   var offset = argsIndex;
3853   while (++rightIndex < rightLength) {
3854     result[offset + rightIndex] = partials[rightIndex];
3855   }
3856   while (++holdersIndex < holdersLength) {
3857     if (isUncurried || argsIndex < argsLength) {
3858       result[offset + holders[holdersIndex]] = args[argsIndex++];
3859     }
3860   }
3861   return result;
3862 }

3888  * @param {Function} func The function to wrap.
3889  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags. See `createWrap` for more details.
3890  * @param {*} [thisArg] The `this` binding of `func`.
3891  * @returns {Function} Returns the new wrapped function.
3892  */
3893 function createBind(func, bitmask, thisArg) {
3894   var isBind = bitmask & BIND_FLAG,
3895       Ctor = createCtor(func);
3896 
3897   function wrapper() {
3898     var fn = (this && this !== root && this instanceof wrapper) ? Ctor : func;
3899     return fn.apply(isBind ? thisArg : this, arguments);
3900   }
3901   return wrapper;
3902 }
3903 
3904 /**
3905  * Creates a function that produces an instance of `Ctor` regardless of
3906  * whether it was invoked as part of a `new` expression or by `call` or `apply`.
3907  *
3908  * @private
3909  * @param {Function} Ctor The constructor to wrap.
3910  * @returns {Function} Returns the new wrapped function.
3911  */
3912 function createCtor(Ctor) {
3913   return function() {
3914     // Use a `switch` statement to work with class constructors. See
3915     // http://ecma-international.org/ecma-262/7.0/#sec-ecmascript-function-objects-call-thisargument-argumentslist
3916     // for more details.
3917     var args = arguments;
3918     switch (args.length) {
3919       case 0: return new Ctor;
3920       case 1: return new Ctor(args[0]);
3921       case 2: return new Ctor(args[0], args[1]);
3922       case 3: return new Ctor(args[0], args[1], args[2]);
3923       case 4: return new Ctor(args[0], args[1], args[2], args[3]);
3924       case 5: return new Ctor(args[0], args[1], args[2], args[3], args[4]);
3925       case 6: return new Ctor(args[0], args[1], args[2], args[3], args[4], args[5]);
3926       case 7: return new Ctor(args[0], args[1], args[2], args[3], args[4], args[5], args[6]);
3927     }
3928     var thisBinding = baseCreate(Ctor.prototype),
3929         result = Ctor.apply(thisBinding, args);
3930 
3931     // Mimic the constructor's `return` behavior.
3932     // See https://es5.github.io/#x13.2.2 for more details.
3933     return isObject(result) ? result : thisBinding;
3934   };
3935 }
3936 
3937 /**
3938  * Creates a function that wraps `func` to enable currying.
3939  *
3940  * @private
3941  * @param {Function} func The function to wrap.
3942  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags. See `createWrap` for more details.
3943  * @param {number} arity The arity of `func`.
3944  * @returns {Function} Returns the new wrapped function.
3945  */
3946 function createCurry(func, bitmask, arity) {
3947   var Ctor = createCtor(func);
3948 
3949   function wrapper() {
3950     var length = arguments.length,
3951         args = Array(length),
3952         index = length,
3953         placeholder = getHolder(wrapper);
3954 
3955     while (index--) {
3956       args[index] = arguments[index];
3957     }
3958     var holders = (length < 3 && args[0] !== placeholder && args[length - 1] !== placeholder)
3959       ? []
3960       : replaceHolders(args, placeholder);
3961 
3962     length -= holders.length;
3963     if (length < arity) {
3964       return createRecurry(
3965         func, bitmask, createHybrid, wrapper.placeholder, undefined,
3966         args, holders, undefined, undefined, arity - length);
3967     }
3968     var fn = (this && this !== root && this instanceof wrapper) ? Ctor : func;
3969     return apply(fn, this, args);
3970   }
3971   return wrapper;
3972 }
3973 
3974 /**
3975  * Creates a function that wraps `func` to invoke it with optional `this`
3976  * binding of `thisArg`, partial application, and currying.
3977  *
3978  * @private
3979  * @param {Function|string} func The function or method name to wrap.
3980  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags. See `createWrap` for more details.
3981  * @param {*} [thisArg] The `this` binding of `func`.
3982  * @param {Array} [partials] The arguments to prepend to those provided to
3983  *  the new function.
3984  * @param {Array} [holders] The `partials` placeholder indexes.
3985  * @param {Array} [partialsRight] The arguments to append to those provided
3986  *  to the new function.
3987  * @param {Array} [holdersRight] The `partialsRight` placeholder indexes.
3988  * @param {Array} [argPos] The argument positions of the new function.
3989  * @param {number} [ary] The arity cap of `func`.
3990  * @param {number} [arity] The arity of `func`.
3991  * @returns {Function} Returns the new wrapped function.
3992  */
3993 function createHybrid(func, bitmask, thisArg, partials, holders, partialsRight, holdersRight, argPos, ary, arity) {
3994   var isAry = bitmask & ARY_FLAG,
3995       isBind = bitmask & BIND_FLAG,
3996       isBindKey = bitmask & BIND_KEY_FLAG,
3997       isCurried = bitmask & (CURRY_FLAG | CURRY_RIGHT_FLAG),
3998       isFlip = bitmask & FLIP_FLAG,
3999       Ctor = isBindKey ? undefined : createCtor(func);
4000 
4001   function wrapper() {
4002     var length = arguments.length,
4003         args = Array(length),
4004         index = length;
4005 
4006     while (index--) {
4007       args[index] = arguments[index];
4008     }
4009     if (isCurried) {
4010       var placeholder = getHolder(wrapper),
4011           holdersCount = countHolders(args, placeholder);
4012     }
4013     if (partials) {
4014       args = composeArgs(args, partials, holders, isCurried);
4015     }
4016     if (partialsRight) {
4017       args = composeArgsRight(args, partialsRight, holdersRight, isCurried);
4018     }
4019     length -= holdersCount;
4020     if (isCurried && length < arity) {
4021       var newHolders = replaceHolders(args, placeholder);
4022       return createRecurry(
4023         func, bitmask, createHybrid, wrapper.placeholder, thisArg,
4024         args, newHolders, argPos, ary, arity - length
4025       );
4026     }
4027     var thisBinding = isBind ? thisArg : this,
4028         fn = isBindKey ? thisBinding[func] : func;
4029 
4030     length = args.length;
4031     if (argPos) {
4032       args = reorder(args, argPos);
4033     } else if (isFlip && length > 1) {
4034       args.reverse();
4035     }
4036     if (isAry && ary < length) {
4037       args.length = ary;
4038     }
4039     if (this && this !== root && this instanceof wrapper) {
4040       fn = Ctor || createCtor(fn);
4041     }
4042     return fn.apply(thisBinding, args);
4043   }
4044   return wrapper;
4045 }
4046 
4047 /**
4048  * Creates a function that wraps `func` to invoke it with the `this` binding
4049  * of `thisArg` and `partials` prepended to the arguments it receives.
4050  *
4051  * @private
4052  * @param {Function} func The function to wrap.
4053  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags. See `createWrap` for more details.
4054  * @param {*} thisArg The `this` binding of `func`.
4055  * @param {Array} partials The arguments to prepend to those provided to
4056  *  the new function.
4057  * @returns {Function} Returns the new wrapped function.
4058  */
4059 function createPartial(func, bitmask, thisArg, partials) {
4060   var isBind = bitmask & BIND_FLAG,
4061       Ctor = createCtor(func);
4062 
4063   function wrapper() {
4064     var argsIndex = -1,
4065         argsLength = arguments.length,
4066         leftIndex = -1,
4067         leftLength = partials.length,
4068         args = Array(leftLength + argsLength),
4069         fn = (this && this !== root && this instanceof wrapper) ? Ctor : func;
4070 
4071     while (++leftIndex < leftLength) {
4072       args[leftIndex] = partials[leftIndex];
4073     }
4074     while (argsLength--) {
4075       args[leftIndex++] = arguments[++argsIndex];
4076     }
4077     return apply(fn, isBind ? thisArg : this, args);
4078   }
4079   return wrapper;
4080 }
4081 
4082 /**
4083  * Creates a function that wraps `func` to continue currying.
4084  *
4085  * @private
4086  * @param {Function} func The function to wrap.
4087  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags. See `createWrap` for more details.
4088  * @param {Function} wrapFunc The function to create the `func` wrapper.
4089  * @param {*} placeholder The placeholder value.
4090  * @param {*} [thisArg] The `this` binding of `func`.
4091  * @param {Array} [partials] The arguments to prepend to those provided to
4092  *  the new function.
4093  * @param {Array} [holders] The `partials` placeholder indexes.
4094  * @param {Array} [argPos] The argument positions of the new function.
4095  * @param {number} [ary] The arity cap of `func`.
4096  * @param {number} [arity] The arity of `func`.
4097  * @returns {Function} Returns the new wrapped function.
4098  */
4099 function createRecurry(func, bitmask, wrapFunc, placeholder, thisArg, partials, holders, argPos, ary, arity) {
4100   var isCurry = bitmask & CURRY_FLAG,
4101       newHolders = isCurry ? holders : undefined,
4102       newHoldersRight = isCurry ? undefined : holders,
4103       newPartials = isCurry ? partials : undefined,
4104       newPartialsRight = isCurry ? undefined : partials;
4105 
4106   bitmask |= (isCurry ? PARTIAL_FLAG : PARTIAL_RIGHT_FLAG);
4107   bitmask &= ~(isCurry ? PARTIAL_RIGHT_FLAG : PARTIAL_FLAG);
4108 
4109   if (!(bitmask & CURRY_BOUND_FLAG)) {
4110     bitmask &= ~(BIND_FLAG | BIND_KEY_FLAG);
4111   }
4112 
4113   var result = wrapFunc(func, bitmask, thisArg, newPartials, newHolders, newPartialsRight, newHoldersRight, argPos, ary, arity);
4114   result.placeholder = placeholder;
4115   return setWrapToString(result, func, bitmask);
4116 }
4117 
4118 /**
4119  * Creates a function that either curries or invokes `func` with optional
4120  * `this` binding and partially applied arguments.
4121  *
4122  * @private
4123  * @param {Function|string} func The function or method name to wrap.
4124  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags.
4125  *  The bitmask may be composed of the following flags:
4126  *     1 - `_.bind`
4127  *     2 - `_.bindKey`
4128  *     4 - `_.curry` or `_.curryRight` of a bound function
4129  *     8 - `_.curry`
4130  *    16 - `_.curryRight`
4131  *    32 - `_.partial`
4132  *    64 - `_.partialRight`
4133  *   128 - `_.rearg`
4134  *   256 - `_.ary`
4135  *   512 - `_.flip`
4136  * @param {*} [thisArg] The `this` binding of `func`.
4137  * @param {Array} [partials] The arguments to be partially applied.
4138  * @param {Array} [holders] The `partials` placeholder indexes.
4139  * @param {Array} [argPos] The argument positions of the new function.
4140  * @param {number} [ary] The arity cap of `func`.
4141  * @param {number} [arity] The arity of `func`.
4142  * @returns {Function} Returns the new wrapped function.
4143  */
4144 function createWrap(func, bitmask, thisArg, partials, holders, argPos, ary, arity) {
4145   var isBindKey = bitmask & BIND_KEY_FLAG;
4146   if (!isBindKey && typeof func != 'function') {
4147     throw new TypeError(FUNC_ERROR_TEXT);
4148   }
4149   var length = partials ? partials.length : 0;
4150   if (!length) {
4151     bitmask &= ~(PARTIAL_FLAG | PARTIAL_RIGHT_FLAG);
4152     partials = holders = undefined;
4153   }
4154   ary = ary === undefined ? ary : nativeMax(toInteger(ary), 0);
4155   arity = arity === undefined ? arity : toInteger(arity);
4156   length -= holders ? holders.length : 0;
4157 
4158   if (bitmask & PARTIAL_RIGHT_FLAG) {
4159     var partialsRight = partials,
4160         holdersRight = holders;
4161 
4162     partials = holders = undefined;
4163   }
4164 
4165   var newData = [
4166     func, bitmask, thisArg, partials, holders, partialsRight, holdersRight,
4167     argPos, ary, arity
4168   ];
4169 
4170   func = newData[0];
4171   bitmask = newData[1];
4172   thisArg = newData[2];
4173   partials = newData[3];
4174   holders = newData[4];
4175   arity = newData[9] = newData[9] == null
4176     ? (isBindKey ? 0 : func.length)
4177     : nativeMax(newData[9] - length, 0);
4178 
4179   if (!arity && bitmask & (CURRY_FLAG | CURRY_RIGHT_FLAG)) {
4180     bitmask &= ~(CURRY_FLAG | CURRY_RIGHT_FLAG);
4181   }
4182   if (!bitmask || bitmask == BIND_FLAG) {
4183     var result = createBind(func, bitmask, thisArg);
4184   } else if (bitmask == CURRY_FLAG || bitmask == CURRY_RIGHT_FLAG) {
4185     result = createCurry(func, bitmask, arity);
4186   } else if ((bitmask == PARTIAL_FLAG || bitmask == (BIND_FLAG | PARTIAL_FLAG)) && !holders.length) {
4187     result = createPartial(func, bitmask, thisArg, partials);
4188   } else {
4189     result = createHybrid.apply(undefined, newData);
4190   }
4191   return setWrapToString(result, func, bitmask);
4192 }
4193 
4194 /**
4195  * Gets the argument placeholder value for `func`.
4196  *
4197  * @private
4198  * @param {Function} func The function to inspect.
4199  * @returns {*} Returns the placeholder value.
4200  */
4201 function getHolder(func) {
4202   var object = func;
4203   return object.placeholder;
4204 }

4206 /**
4207  * Gets the native function at `key` of `object`.
4208  *
4209  * @private
4210  * @param {Object} object The object to query.
4211  * @param {string} key The key of the method to get.
4212  * @returns {*} Returns the function if it's native, else `undefined`.
4213  */
4214 function getNative(object, key) {
4215   var value = getValue(object, key);
4216   return baseIsNative(value) ? value : undefined;
4217 }

4219 /**
4220  * Extracts wrapper details from the `source` body comment.
4221  *
4222  * @private
4223  * @param {string} source The source to inspect.
4224  * @returns {Array} Returns the wrapper details.
4225  */
4226 function getWrapDetails(source) {
4227   var match = source.match(reWrapDetails);
4228   return match ? match[1].split(reSplitDetails) : [];
4229 }
4230 
4231 /**
4232  * Inserts wrapper `details` in a comment at the top of the `source` body.
4233  *
4234  * @private
4235  * @param {string} source The source to modify.
4236  * @returns {Array} details The details to insert.
4237  * @returns {string} Returns the modified source.
4238  */
4239 function insertWrapDetails(source, details) {
4240   var length = details.length,
4241       lastIndex = length - 1;
4242 
4243   details[lastIndex] = (length > 1 ? '& ' : '') + details[lastIndex];
4244   details = details.join(length > 2 ? ', ' : ' ');
4245   return source.replace(reWrapComment, '{\n/* [wrapped with ' + details + '] */\n');
4246 }

4248 /**
4249  * Checks if `value` is a valid array-like index.
4250  *
4251  * @private
4252  * @param {*} value The value to check.
4253  * @param {number} [length=MAX_SAFE_INTEGER] The upper bounds of a valid index.
4254  * @returns {boolean} Returns `true` if `value` is a valid index, else `false`.
4255  */
4256 function isIndex(value, length) {
4257   length = length == null ? MAX_SAFE_INTEGER : length;
4258   return !!length &&
4259     (typeof value == 'number' || reIsUint.test(value)) &&
4260     (value > -1 && value % 1 == 0 && value < length);
4261 }
4262 
4263 /**
4264  * Checks if `func` has its source masked.
4265  *
4266  * @private
4267  * @param {Function} func The function to check.
4268  * @returns {boolean} Returns `true` if `func` is masked, else `false`.
4269  */
4270 function isMasked(func) {
4271   return !!maskSrcKey && (maskSrcKey in func);
4272 }
4273 
4274 /**
4275  * Reorder `array` according to the specified indexes where the element at
4276  * the first index is assigned as the first element, the element at
4277  * the second index is assigned as the second element, and so on.
4278  *
4279  * @private
4280  * @param {Array} array The array to reorder.
4281  * @param {Array} indexes The arranged array indexes.
4282  * @returns {Array} Returns `array`.
4283  */
4284 function reorder(array, indexes) {
4285   var arrLength = array.length,
4286       length = nativeMin(indexes.length, arrLength),
4287       oldArray = copyArray(array);
4288 
4289   while (length--) {
4290     var index = indexes[length];
4291     array[length] = isIndex(index, arrLength) ? oldArray[index] : undefined;
4292   }
4293   return array;
4294 }
4295 
4296 /**
4297  * Sets the `toString` method of `wrapper` to mimic the source of `reference`
4298  * with wrapper details in a comment at the top of the source body.
4299  *
4300  * @private
4301  * @param {Function} wrapper The function to modify.
4302  * @param {Function} reference The reference function.
4303  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags. See `createWrap` for more details.
4304  * @returns {Function} Returns `wrapper`.
4305  */
4306 var setWrapToString = !defineProperty ? identity : function(wrapper, reference, bitmask) {
4307   var source = (reference + '');
4308   return defineProperty(wrapper, 'toString', {
4309     'configurable': true,
4310     'enumerable': false,
4311     'value': constant(insertWrapDetails(source, updateWrapDetails(getWrapDetails(source), bitmask)))
4312   });
4313 };
4314 
4315 /**
4316  * Converts `func` to its source code.
4317  *
4318  * @private
4319  * @param {Function} func The function to process.
4320  * @returns {string} Returns the source code.
4321  */
4322 function toSource(func) {
4323   if (func != null) {
4324     try {
4325       return funcToString.call(func);
4326     } catch (e) {}
4327     try {
4328       return (func + '');
4329     } catch (e) {}
4330   }
4331   return '';
4332 }
4333 
4334 /**
4335  * Updates wrapper `details` based on `bitmask` flags.
4336  *
4337  * @private
4338  * @returns {Array} details The details to modify.
4339  * @param {number} bitmask The bitmask flags. See `createWrap` for more details.
4340  * @returns {Array} Returns `details`.
4341  */
4342 function updateWrapDetails(details, bitmask) {
4343   arrayEach(wrapFlags, function(pair) {
4344     var value = '_.' + pair[0];
4345     if ((bitmask & pair[1]) && !arrayIncludes(details, value)) {
4346       details.push(value);
4347     }
4348   });
4349   return details.sort();
4350 }
4351 
4352 /**
4353  * Creates a function that accepts arguments of `func` and either invokes
4354  * `func` returning its result, if at least `arity` number of arguments have
4355  * been provided, or returns a function that accepts the remaining `func`
4356  * arguments, and so on. The arity of `func` may be specified if `func.length`
4357  * is not sufficient.
4358  *
4359  * The `_.curry.placeholder` value, which defaults to `_` in monolithic builds,
4360  * may be used as a placeholder for provided arguments.
4361  *
4362  * **Note:** This method doesn't set the "length" property of curried functions.
4363  *
4364  * @static
4365  * @memberOf _
4366  * @since 2.0.0
4367  * @category Function
4368  * @param {Function} func The function to curry.
4369  * @param {number} [arity=func.length] The arity of `func`.
4370  * @param- {Object} [guard] Enables use as an iteratee for methods like `_.map`.
4371  * @returns {Function} Returns the new curried function.
4372  * @example
4373  *
4374  * var abc = function(a, b, c) {
4375  *   return [a, b, c];
4376  * };
4377  *
4378  * var curried = _.curry(abc);
4379  *
4380  * curried(1)(2)(3);
4381  * // => [1, 2, 3]
4382  *
4383  * curried(1, 2)(3);
4384  * // => [1, 2, 3]
4385  *
4386  * curried(1, 2, 3);
4387  * // => [1, 2, 3]
4388  *
4389  * // Curried with placeholders.
4390  * curried(1)(_, 3)(2);
4391  * // => [1, 2, 3]
4392  */
4393 function curry(func, arity, guard) {
4394   arity = guard ? undefined : arity;
4395   var result = createWrap(func, CURRY_FLAG, undefined, undefined, undefined, undefined, undefined, arity);
4396   result.placeholder = curry.placeholder;
4397   return result;
4398 }
4399 
4400 /**
4401  * Checks if `value` is classified as a `Function` object.
4402  *
4403  * @static
4404  * @memberOf _
4405  * @since 0.1.0
4406  * @category Lang
4407  * @param {*} value The value to check.
4408  * @returns {boolean} Returns `true` if `value` is a function, else `false`.
4409  * @example
4410  *
4411  * _.isFunction(_);
4412  * // => true
4413  *
4414  * _.isFunction(/abc/);
4415  * // => false
4416  */
4417 function isFunction(value) {
4418   // The use of `Object#toString` avoids issues with the `typeof` operator
4419   // in Safari 8-9 which returns 'object' for typed array and other constructors.
4420   var tag = isObject(value) ? objectToString.call(value) : '';
4421   return tag == funcTag || tag == genTag;
4422 }
4423 
4424 /**
4425  * Checks if `value` is the
4426  * [language type](http://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/7.0/#sec-ecmascript-language-types)
4427  * of `Object`. (e.g. arrays, functions, objects, regexes, `new Number(0)`, and `new String('')`)
4428  *
4429  * @static
4430  * @memberOf _
4431  * @since 0.1.0
4432  * @category Lang
4433  * @param {*} value The value to check.
4434  * @returns {boolean} Returns `true` if `value` is an object, else `false`.
4435  * @example
4436  *
4437  * _.isObject({});
4438  * // => true
4439  *
4440  * _.isObject([1, 2, 3]);
4441  * // => true
4442  *
4443  * _.isObject(_.noop);
4444  * // => true
4445  *
4446  * _.isObject(null);
4447  * // => false
4448  */
4449 function isObject(value) {
4450   var type = typeof value;
4451   return !!value && (type == 'object' || type == 'function');
4452 }

4454 /**
4455  * Checks if `value` is object-like. A value is object-like if it's not `null`
4456  * and has a `typeof` result of "object".
4457  *
4458  * @static
4459  * @memberOf _
4460  * @since 4.0.0
4461  * @category Lang
4462  * @param {*} value The value to check.
4463  * @returns {boolean} Returns `true` if `value` is object-like, else `false`.
4464  * @example
4465  *
4466  * _.isObjectLike({});
4467  * // => true
4468  *
4469  * _.isObjectLike([1, 2, 3]);
4470  * // => true
4471  *
4472  * _.isObjectLike(_.noop);
4473  * // => false
4474  *
4475  * _.isObjectLike(null);
4476  * // => false
4477  */
4478 function isObjectLike(value) {
4479   return !!value && typeof value == 'object';
4480 }
4481 
4482 /**
4483  * Checks if `value` is classified as a `Symbol` primitive or object.
4484  *
4485  * @static
4486  * @memberOf _
4487  * @since 4.0.0
4488  * @category Lang
4489  * @param {*} value The value to check.
4490  * @returns {boolean} Returns `true` if `value` is a symbol, else `false`.
4491  * @example
4492  *
4493  * _.isSymbol(Symbol.iterator);
4494  * // => true
4495  *
4496  * _.isSymbol('abc');
4497  * // => false
4498  */
4499 function isSymbol(value) {
4500   return typeof value == 'symbol' ||

4504 /**
4505  * Converts `value` to a finite number.
4506  *
4507  * @static
4508  * @memberOf _
4509  * @since 4.12.0
4510  * @category Lang
4511  * @param {*} value The value to convert.
4512  * @returns {number} Returns the converted number.
4513  * @example
4514  *
4515  * _.toFinite(3.2);
4516  * // => 3.2
4517  *
4518  * _.toFinite(Number.MIN_VALUE);
4519  * // => 5e-324
4520  *
4521  * _.toFinite(Infinity);
4522  * // => 1.7976931348623157e+308
4523  *
4524  * _.toFinite('3.2');
4525  * // => 3.2
4526  */
4527 function toFinite(value) {
4528   if (!value) {
4529     return value === 0 ? value : 0;
4530   }
4531   value = toNumber(value);
4532   if (value === INFINITY || value === -INFINITY) {
4533     var sign = (value < 0 ? -1 : 1);
4534     return sign * MAX_INTEGER;
4535   }
4536   return value === value ? value : 0;
4537 }

4541  *
4542  * **Note:** This method is loosely based on
4543  * [`ToInteger`](http://www.ecma-international.org/ecma-262/7.0/#sec-tointeger).
4544  *
4545  * @static

4547  * @since 4.0.0
4548  * @category Lang

4553  * _.toInteger(3.2);
4554  * // => 3
4555  *
4556  * _.toInteger(Number.MIN_VALUE);
4557  * // => 0
4558  *
4559  * _.toInteger(Infinity);
4560  * // => 1.7976931348623157e+308
4561  *
4562  * _.toInteger('3.2');
4563  * // => 3
4564  */
4565 function toInteger(value) {
4566   var result = toFinite(value),
4567       remainder = result % 1;
4568 
4569   return result === result ? (remainder ? result - remainder : result) : 0;

4572 /**
4573  * Converts `value` to a number.
4574  *
4575  * @static
4576  * @memberOf _
4577  * @since 4.0.0
4578  * @category Lang
4579  * @param {*} value The value to process.
4580  * @returns {number} Returns the number.
4581  * @example
4582  *
4583  * _.toNumber(3.2);
4584  * // => 3.2
4585  *
4586  * _.toNumber(Number.MIN_VALUE);
4587  * // => 5e-324
4588  *
4589  * _.toNumber(Infinity);
4590  * // => Infinity
4591  *
4592  * _.toNumber('3.2');
4593  * // => 3.2
4594  */
4595 function toNumber(value) {
4596   if (typeof value == 'number') {
4597     return value;
4598   }
4599   if (isSymbol(value)) {
4600     return NAN;
4601   }
4602   if (isObject(value)) {
4603     var other = typeof value.valueOf == 'function' ? value.valueOf() : value;
4604     value = isObject(other) ? (other + '') : other;
4605   }
4606   if (typeof value != 'string') {
4607     return value === 0 ? value : +value;
4608   }
4609   value = value.replace(reTrim, '');
4610   var isBinary = reIsBinary.test(value);
4611   return (isBinary || reIsOctal.test(value))
4612     ? freeParseInt(value.slice(2), isBinary ? 2 : 8)
4613     : (reIsBadHex.test(value) ? NAN : +value);
4614 }

5795 	  function isNode(propValue) {
5796 	    switch (typeof propValue) {
5797 	      case 'number':
5798 	      case 'string':
5799 	      case 'undefined':
5800 	        return true;
5801 	      case 'boolean':
5802 	        return !propValue;
5803 	      case 'object':
5804 	        if (Array.isArray(propValue)) {
5805 	          return propValue.every(isNode);
5806 	        }
5807 	        if (propValue === null || isValidElement(propValue)) {
5808 	          return true;
5809 	        }
5810 	
5811 	        var iteratorFn = getIteratorFn(propValue);
5812 	        if (iteratorFn) {
5813 	          var iterator = iteratorFn.call(propValue);
5814 	          var step;
5815 	          if (iteratorFn !== propValue.entries) {
5816 	            while (!(step = iterator.next()).done) {
5817 	              if (!isNode(step.value)) {
5818 	                return false;
5819 	              }
5820 	            }
5821 	          } else {
5822 	            // Iterator will provide entry [k,v] tuples rather than values.
5823 	            while (!(step = iterator.next()).done) {
5824 	              var entry = step.value;
5825 	              if (entry) {
5826 	                if (!isNode(entry[1])) {
5827 	                  return false;
5828 	                }
5829 	              }
5830 	            }
5831 	          }
5832 	        } else {
5833 	          return false;
5834 	        }
5835 	
5836 	        return true;
5837 	      default:
5838 	        return false;
5839 	    }
5840 	  }

5842 	  function isSymbol(propType, propValue) {
5843 	    // Native Symbol.
5844 	    if (propType === 'symbol') {
5845 	      return true;
5846 	    }
5847 	
5848 	    // 19.4.3.5 Symbol.prototype[@@toStringTag] === 'Symbol'
5849 	    if (propValue['@@toStringTag'] === 'Symbol') {
5850 	      return true;
5851 	    }
5852 	
5853 	    // Fallback for non-spec compliant Symbols which are polyfilled.
5854 	    if (typeof Symbol === 'function' && propValue instanceof Symbol) {
5855 	      return true;
5856 	    }
5857 	
5858 	    return false;
5859 	  }
5860 	
5861 	  // Equivalent of `typeof` but with special handling for array and regexp.
5862 	  function getPropType(propValue) {
5863 	    var propType = typeof propValue;
5864 	    if (Array.isArray(propValue)) {
5865 	      return 'array';
5866 	    }
5867 	    if (propValue instanceof RegExp) {
5868 	      // Old webkits (at least until Android 4.0) return 'function' rather than
5869 	      // 'object' for typeof a RegExp. We'll normalize this here so that /bla/
5870 	      // passes PropTypes.object.
5871 	      return 'object';
5872 	    }
5873 	    if (isSymbol(propType, propValue)) {
5874 	      return 'symbol';
5875 	    }
5876 	    return propType;
5877 	  }
5878 	
5879 	  // This handles more types than `getPropType`. Only used for error messages.
5880 	  // See `createPrimitiveTypeChecker`.
5881 	  function getPreciseType(propValue) {
5882 	    if (typeof propValue === 'undefined' || propValue === null) {
5883 	      return '' + propValue;
5884 	    }
5885 	    var propType = getPropType(propValue);
5886 	    if (propType === 'object') {
5887 	      if (propValue instanceof Date) {
5888 	        return 'date';
5889 	      } else if (propValue instanceof RegExp) {
5890 	        return 'regexp';
5891 	      }
5892 	    }
5893 	    return propType;
5894 	  }

7634 // :: - Style modules encapsulate a set of CSS rules defined from
7635 // JavaScript. Their definitions are only available in a given DOM
7636 // root after it has been _mounted_ there with `StyleModule.mount`.
7637 //
7638 // Style modules should be created once and stored somewhere, as
7639 // opposed to re-creating them every time you need them. The amount of
7640 // CSS rules generated for a given DOM root is bounded by the amount
7641 // of style modules that were used. So to avoid leaking rules, don't
7642 // create these dynamically, but treat them as one-time allocations.
7643 class StyleModule {
7644   // :: (Object<Style>, ?{finish: ?(string) ‚Üí string})
7645   // Create a style module from the given spec.
7646   //
7647   // When `finish` is given, it is called on regular (non-`@`)
7648   // selectors (after `&` expansion) to compute the final selector.
7649   constructor(spec, options) {
7650     this.rules = []
7651     let {finish} = options || {}
7652 
7653     function splitSelector(selector) {
7654       return /^@/.test(selector) ? [selector] : selector.split(/,\s*/)
7655     }
7656 
7657     function render(selectors, spec, target, isKeyframes) {
7658       let local = [], isAt = /^@(\w+)\b/.exec(selectors[0]), keyframes = isAt && isAt[1] == "keyframes"
7659       if (isAt && spec == null) return target.push(selectors[0] + ";")
7660       for (let prop in spec) {
7661         let value = spec[prop]
7662         if (/&/.test(prop)) {
7663           render(prop.split(/,\s*/).map(part => selectors.map(sel => part.replace(/&/, sel))).reduce((a, b) => a.concat(b)),
7664                  value, target)
7665         } else if (value && typeof value == "object") {
7666           if (!isAt) throw new RangeError("The value of a property (" + prop + ") should be a primitive value.")
7667           render(splitSelector(prop), value, local, keyframes)
7668         } else if (value != null) {
7669           local.push(prop.replace(/_.*/, "").replace(/[A-Z]/g, l => "-" + l.toLowerCase()) + ": " + value + ";")
7670         }
7671       }
7672       if (local.length || keyframes) {
7673         target.push((finish && !isAt && !isKeyframes ? selectors.map(finish) : selectors).join(", ") +
7674                     " {" + local.join(" ") + "}")
7675       }
7676     }
7677 
7678     for (let prop in spec) render(splitSelector(prop), spec[prop], this.rules)
7679   }
7680 
7681   // :: () ‚Üí string
7682   // Returns a string containing the module's CSS rules.
7683   getRules() { return this.rules.join("\n") }
7684 
7685   // :: () ‚Üí string

7687   static newName() {
7688     let id = top[COUNT] || 1
7689     top[COUNT] = id + 1
7690     return C + id.toString(36)
7691   }

7693   // :: (union<Document, ShadowRoot>, union<[StyleModule], StyleModule>, ?{nonce: ?string})
7694   //
7695   // Mount the given set of modules in the given DOM root, which ensures
7696   // that the CSS rules defined by the module are available in that
7697   // context.
7698   //
7699   // Rules are only added to the document once per root.
7700   //
7701   // Rule order will follow the order of the modules, so that rules from
7702   // modules later in the array take precedence of those from earlier
7703   // modules. If you call this function multiple times for the same root
7704   // in a way that changes the order of already mounted modules, the old
7705   // order will be changed.
7706   //
7707   // If a Content Security Policy nonce is provided, it is added to
7708   // the `<style>` tag generated by the library.
7709   static mount(root, modules, options) {
7710     let set = root[SET], nonce = options && options.nonce
7711     if (!set) set = new StyleSet(root, nonce)
7712     else if (nonce) set.setNonce(nonce)
7713     set.mount(Array.isArray(modules) ? modules : [modules])
7714   }

7776 // Style::Object<union<Style,string>>
7777 //
7778 // A style is an object that, in the simple case, maps CSS property
7779 // names to strings holding their values, as in `{color: "red",
7780 // fontWeight: "bold"}`. The property names can be given in
7781 // camel-case‚Äîthe library will insert a dash before capital letters
7782 // when converting them to CSS.
7783 //
7784 // If you include an underscore in a property name, it and everything
7785 // after it will be removed from the output, which can be useful when
7786 // providing a property multiple times, for browser compatibility
7787 // reasons.
7788 //
7789 // A property in a style object can also be a sub-selector, which
7790 // extends the current context to add a pseudo-selector or a child
7791 // selector. Such a property should contain a `&` character, which
7792 // will be replaced by the current selector. For example `{"&:before":
7793 // {content: '"hi"'}}`. Sub-selectors and regular properties can
7794 // freely be mixed in a given object. Any property containing a `&` is
7795 // assumed to be a sub-selector.
7796 //
7797 // Finally, a property can specify an @-block to be wrapped around the
7798 // styles defined inside the object that's the property's value. For
